         <abstract>
            <p>The purpose of this paper is to investigate cardinal interpolation using locally supported piecewise polynomials. In particular, the notion of a commutator is introduced and its connection with the Marsden identity is observed. The order of a commutator is shown to be equivalent to the Strang and Fix conditions that arise in the study of the local approximation orders using quasi-interpolants. We also prove that scaled cardinal interpolants give these local approximation orders.</p>
          </abstract>
